TERMINALIA. Pygofer (
Fig. 13
) moderately produced posteriorly; broadly rounded distally, angulate at apex; with dispersed microsetae and ventroapically with macrosetae; ventral margin with elongate sinuous process originated from basal third, reaching apical margin, apex acute. Subgenital plate (
Fig. 15
) not fused to its counterpart; triangular; with numerous dispersed microsetae and few macrosetae near apex; dorsal surface with small tooth at median third; plate (
Fig. 13
) extending as far posteriorly as pygofer apex. Style (
Fig. 16
) elongate, attaining tooth of plate; extremely expanded apically, forming conspicuous lobe. Connective (
Fig. 16
) Y-shaped; very short; stalk without median dorsal keel.Aedeagus symmetrical; shaft (
Fig. 17
) short, straight, without lateral expansions, with dorsal preapical hump; apical region expanded; in ventral view (
Fig. 18
), shaft somewhat anchor-shaped apically, with pair of preapical short acute processes directed anteriorad.

